snippet.textDisplay:
If I had a boyfriend that cheated on me there are two scenarios.
1. If he cheated and he told me (within 2 - 3 weeks), I would break up with him, be ANGRY of course, but I'd break up very respectfully, if we were livng together, if we shared money etc, I would make sure that there are no fights from my side, everything would be evenly split or/and stuff that is his would be his no arguement.
2. If he cheated on me and DIDN'T tell me, and I found out, I would never forgive him and I would hate him.
Remember, if you're cheating, you are not happy, so why are you still in this relationship?

snippet.textDisplay: I’ve cheated in the past and I can say that I disagree with almost all of these people. I cheated on someone who trusted me and was there for me, with someone toxic from my past. If I was to make an excuse it would be that I was just not ready to move on. But, there’s truly no excuses for the pain I caused that person. He’s still my friend to this day which continues to show me that he truly did love me. And it kills me to know that I caused that pain that he had and that I’m the reason he’s guarded in love. It kills me that instead of being honest and breaking up with him, I stayed with him and cheated for my own selfishness. I will always say that is the worst thing that I’ve ever done in my entire life and it crushes my heart. I could never do that to anyone again, and I could never deal with someone doing it to me. Within the relationship with the person I cheated on, I selfishly wanted him for the attention, not to give it back. I was a cruel person. Cheating is never okay. Ever. (I don’t agree once a cheater always a cheater bc I was 15 when it happened and I could never allow myself to do that again. I’m currently engaged to my boyfriend of 3 years and we’re planning to get married in a year or so. I’ve never even allowed myself to hang out with guys or put myself into a position to be able to cheat because I know the pain it caused.)

snippet.textDisplay:
Cheating is one of the few things in this world that is black and white.
It's always wrong.
It's not a mistake, it's a choice. You make the choice to hurt someone.
If someone isn't satisfying your needs or you don't feel you love them anymore please just break up with them. Cheating does irreversible psychological damage to people that will usually haunt them for the rest of their lives. I have absolutely 0 empathy for cheaters, and if you were honestly in a relationship and came to the conclusion that cheating was the best course of action, do the world a favor and stay single.
